Roles & directory structure — Must

What is a Role?

Roles = Way to organize playbook into reusable, structured components.

Simple analogy:

Playbook = entire recipe book
Role     = one recipe (nginx, mysql, java)

create a role:

# creates full folder structure automatically
ansible-galaxy init nginx
ansible-galaxy init mysql
ansible-galaxy init java

Role directory structure:

roles/
└── nginx/                    # role name
    ├── tasks/
    │   └── main.yml          # main tasks
    ├── handlers/
    │   └── main.yml          # handlers
    ├── vars/
    │   └── main.yml          # variables
    ├── defaults/
    │   └── main.yml          # default variables (lowest priority)
    ├── templates/
    │   └── nginx.conf.j2     # jinja2 templates
    ├── files/
    │   └── nginx.conf        # static files
    ├── meta/
    │   └── main.yml          # role dependencies
    └── README.md

Each file does:

| Folder              | Purpose                                   |
|---------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| tasks/main.yml      | Main tasks to execute                     |
| handlers/main.yml   | Handlers (notify triggers)                |
| vars/main.yml       | Role variables (high priority)            |
| defaults/main.yml   | Default variables (low priority, overridable) |
| templates/          | Jinja2 template files (.j2)               |
| files/              | Static files to copy                      |
| meta/main.yml       | Role dependencies                         |


